{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-1393"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of carpets and rugs"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1393"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :textiles/carpets-rugs
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :labor-standards :materials-traceability]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :carpet-rug-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "CarpetAdvisor ⊣ Carpet & Rug Plant Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for carpet/rug manufacturing (tufting machines, weaving looms,
 backing lines; woven/tufted carpet and rug output) -- not direct
 tufting/weaving/backing-line control authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Twelve concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct tufting/
 weaving/backing-line-equipment control), permanent direct-operate
 block, independent equipment verification/registration before
 maintenance scheduling, independent batch verification/registration
 before shipment coordination, independent shipment-area recompute
 against the batch's own logged area, double-schedule guard,
 quality-grade validation, pile-density plausibility validation,
 tuft-bind-strength plausibility validation, and defect-rate
 plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging (equipment-safety /
 quality-defect) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor;
 `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
